FuncDef:
The framed-ip urpf disable command disables URPF when IP addresses are delivered by the RADIUS server.
The undo framed-ip urpf disable command restores the default configuration.
By default, URPF is enabled when IP addresses are delivered by the RADIUS server.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
When IP addresses are delivered by the RADIUS server, by default, URPF is enabled to check the source addresses of users during their login. To disable URPF during user login, run the framed-ip urpf disable command.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
